SHORT SENTENCE OF ATTACKERS TOTALLY INAPPROPRIATE
KORT VONNIS VIR AANVALLERS TOTAAL ONVOLDOENDE 13-04-2018 These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. To learn how you can use Content.ad to drive visitors to your content or add this service to your site, please contact us at info@content.ad. Family-Friendly Content Only recommend family-friendly content Website owners select the type of content that appears in our units. However, if you would like to ensure that Content.ad always displays family-friendly content on this device, regardless of what site you are on, check the option below. Learn More FRONT NATIONAL regards the sentencing of the attackers of two elderly people in the Modimolle court as shockingly inappropriate. Mr Edwin Grobler (83) and his wife Petro (79) was attacked at the Settler’s Hotel in December of 2016. During the attack mr Grobler was beaten over the head to such an extend that his hearing aid fell out of his ear. Simon Tito Nkuna and Ronald Lebogang Matsebe fled the scene with stolen wrist watches, wallets, a cash register from the bar, bottles of alcohol and a DVD player. Social workers testified to the trauma of the victims during and following the attack. Magistrate Pieter Manthatha sentenced the two attackers to 3 years imprisonment of which they have to serve only 6 months before applying for parole. Such a sentence is completely inappropriate. Front National asked the opinion of experienced legal experts who agreed that a sentence of at least 6 years direct imprisonment for a first offense, and if previously sentenced, an even longer term of imprisonment would be regarded as suitable punishment. A sentence such as this will undoubtedly send a message to violent criminals that they can get away with behavior such as this. Front National condemns this sentence by Magistrate Manthatha in the strongest possible terms. +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ Front Nasionaal beskou die vonnisoplegging van die aanvallers van twee bejaardes in Modimolle as skokkend onvanpas. Mnr Edwin Grobler (83) en sy vrou, Petro, (79) is in Desember 2016 aangeval by die Settler’s Hotel. Tydens die aanval is meneer Grobler so hard oor die kop geslaan dat sy gehoorstuk uit sy oor geval het. Simon Tito Nkuna en Ronald Lebogang Matsebe het gevlug met gesteelde horlosies, beursies, ‘n kasregister uit die drankwinkel van die hotel, bottels drank en ‘n DVD speler. Maatskaplike werkers het in die hof getuig oor die geweldige trauma wat die twee slagoffers deurgemaak het tydens en sedert die aanval op hulle. Landdros Pieter Manthatha het die twee aanvallers gevonnis tot 3 jaar tronkstraf waarvan hulle slegs 6 maande hoef uit te dien voordat hulle in aanmerking kom vir parool Hierdie vonnis is volgens Front Nasionaal totaal onvanpas en onvoldoende. Ervare regskenners stem met ons saam dat ‘n direkte gevangenisstraf van minstens 6 jaar vir ‘n eerste oortreding, en selfs meer indien daar vorige veroordelings is, in die omstandighede van die saak van pas sou wees. Hierdie vonnis stuur ‘n verkeerde boodskap aan geweldadige misdadigers dat hulle relatief lig van hulle oortreding afkom. Front Nasionaal veroordeel die vonnis wat landdros Manthatha opgelê het ten sterkste. These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. To learn how you can use Content.ad to drive visitors to your content or add this service to your site, please contact us at info@content.ad. Family-Friendly Content Only recommend family-friendly content Website owners select the type of content that appears in our units. However, if you would like to ensure tha